6 ut dicere institueram ‘But as Ι was saying.' A frequent formula of resumption, for the more colloquial ‘ coepi dicere' e. g. Cic. in Verr. II 2, 16, 41 verum ut institui dicere 27, 65. 3, 10, 24 pro Caec. 5,15. See John ad loc. This usage is not met with elsewhere in Tacitus nor in Quintilian.

The preposition before ‘ quibus ' could only have been legitimately omitted, if the antecedent vvere in the same case. Cp. R. V. III p. 728 note 575.
